→ Symmetric reading:
- **Setup aligned with crowded side** = HIGH BAR. (LONG with avg7d > +0.1%, SHORT with avg7d < -0.1%.) The crowd is positioned with you — paying funding for it — and squeeze risk works against you.
- **Setup contrarian to crowded side** = TAILWIND. Fading crowded positioning is positive expected value when the setup itself is structurally valid; the squeeze, when it triggers, fuels your direction.
- **OI 24h Δ aligned with setup direction** = trend confirmation (new participants in your direction). Opposite = yellow flag (your move is unwinding rather than extending).
